                <head>[Enclosure 2]</head>
                <p rend="center">NOTE ON OPINION</p>
                <p>My answer to question No. 1 proceeded upon the assumption that the question
                    related to claims <hi rend="italic">against third parties</hi> as indicated in
                    the instructions. The party giving the indemnity is debarred from claiming
                    against the Procurator General and other Official persons in respect of the
                    goods released. The object of demanding the indemnity would otherwise be
                    defeated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Goldsmith Building. Temple, E. C.</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">3rd June, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Leslie Scott</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
